data.advancedSettings.autocompleteIgnore.comment: Restrict autocomplete results to the current time range

data.advancedSettings.autocompleteIgnore: Disable this property to get autocomplete suggestions from your full dataset, rather than from the current time range. {learnMoreLink}
data.advancedSettings.autocompleteValueS: The method used for querying suggestions for values in KQL autocomplete. Select terms_enum to use the Elasticsearch terms enum API for improved autocomplete suggestion performance. Select terms_agg to use an Elasticsearch terms aggregation. {learnMoreLink}
data.advancedSettings.courier.batchSearc:
Kibana uses a new asynchronous search and infrastructure.
           Enable this option if you prefer to fallback to the legacy synchronous behavior
This setting is deprecated and will be removed in Kibana 8.0.
data.advancedSettings.courier.ignoreFilt: This configuration enhances support for dashboards containing visualizations accessing dissimilar indexes. When disabled, all filters are applied to all visualizations. When enabled, filter(s) will be ignored for a visualization when the visualization's index does not contain the filtering field.
data.advancedSettings.courier.maxRequest: Controls the {maxRequestsLink} setting used for _msearch requests sent by Kibana. Set to 0 to disable this config and use the Elasticsearch default.
data.advancedSettings.courier.requestPre:
Allows you to set which shards handle your search requests.
  • {sessionId}: restricts operations to execute all search requests on the same shards. This has the benefit of reusing shard caches across requests.
  • {custom}: allows you to define a your own preference. Use 'courier:customRequestPreference' to customize your preference value.
  • {none}: means do not set a preference. This might provide better performance because requests can be spread across all shard copies. However, results might be inconsistent because different shards might be in different refresh states.
data.advancedSettings.defaultIndexText: The index to access if no index is set
data.advancedSettings.docTableHighlightT: Highlight results in Discover and Saved Searches Dashboard. Highlighting makes requests slow when working on big documents.
data.advancedSettings.format.defaultType: Map of the format name to use by default for each field type. {defaultFormat} is used if the field type is not mentioned explicitly
data.advancedSettings.histogram.barTarge: Attempt to generate around this many buckets when using "auto" interval in date and numeric histograms
data.advancedSettings.histogram.maxBarsT:
Limits the density of date and number histograms across Kibana
          for better performance using a test query. If the test query would too many buckets,
          the interval between buckets will be increased. This setting applies separately
          to each histogram aggregation, and does not apply to other types of aggregation.
          To find the maximum value of this setting, divide the Elasticsearch 'search.max_buckets'
          value by the maximum number of aggregations in each visualization.
data.advancedSettings.historyLimitText: In fields that have history (e.g. query inputs), show this many recent values
data.advancedSettings.indexPatternPlaceh: The placeholder for the "Index pattern name" field in "Management > Index Patterns > Create Index Pattern".
data.advancedSettings.metaFieldsText: Fields that exist outside of _source to merge into our document when displaying it
data.advancedSettings.pinFiltersText: Whether the filters should have a global state (be pinned) by default
data.advancedSettings.query.allowWildcar: When set, * is allowed as the first character in a query clause. Currently only applies when experimental query features are enabled in the query bar. To disallow leading wildcards in basic lucene queries, use {queryStringOptionsPattern}.

data.advancedSettings.query.queryStringO.text: {optionsLink} for the lucene query string parser. Is only used when "{queryLanguage}" is set to {luceneLanguage}.

data.advancedSettings.searchQueryLanguag: Query language used by the query bar. KQL is a new language built specifically for Kibana.
data.advancedSettings.searchTimeoutDesc: Change the maximum timeout for a search session or set to 0 to disable the timeout and allow queries to run to completion.
data.advancedSettings.shortenFieldsText: Shorten long fields, for example, instead of foo.bar.baz, show f.b.baz
data.advancedSettings.suggestFilterValue: Set this property to false to prevent the filter editor from suggesting values for fields.
